The paper deals with the computation of the optimal correct-decoding exponent for a discrete memoryless channel, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the study of communication rates and convergence, which are topics in coding theory (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of iterative computation suggests a possible connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), while the focus on optimization and convergence could also relate to machine learning (cs.LG).
